# Legacy Systems

## NOMIS

National Offender Management Information System (NOMIS) is the current authority system used for information management and administrations of HMPPS Prisons. Developed by [Syscon](https://syscon.net/), it was originally deployed into HMPPS xx years ago but is suffering from a number of constrains typical for a system of this age:

![](../images/nomis-constraints.png)

As such a programme of work is underway to replace NOMIS with a new suite of digital solutions.

